{"session_id":"svc-1778805701144769769","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-15T00:41:42.151016809Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.5","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"gpt-5.5","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-helix-dfddd64b-20260515T004120-a98eb7dd","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children once more; third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260515T004120-a98eb7dd/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a success. Do not mix implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260515T004120-a98eb7dd/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260515T004120-a98eb7dd/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;To request orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260515T004120-a98eb7dd/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260515T004120-a98eb7dd/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"helix-dfddd64b\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eClarify CRM intake target before creating frame/design artifacts\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\n\u0026lt;context-digest\u0026gt;\u0026#xA;\u0026lt;principles\u0026gt;Design for Change · Design for Simplicity · Validate Your Work · Make Intent Explicit · Prefer Reversible Decisions\u0026lt;/principles\u0026gt;\u0026#xA;\u0026lt;concerns\u0026gt;hugo-hextra | demo-asciinema\u0026lt;/concerns\u0026gt;\u0026#xA;\u0026lt;practices\u0026gt;Define the site\u0026#39;s target audience and what content they need · Theme version: Hextra v0.12.1 — pinned in website/go.mod · Identify which workflows need demo reels — prioritize the \u0026#34;first 5 minutes\u0026#34; experience · Current demos: helix-quickstart (full lifecycle), helix-concerns (drift detection), helix-evolve (requirement threading), helix-experiment (metric-driven optimization)\u0026lt;/practices\u0026gt;\u0026#xA;\u0026lt;governing\u0026gt;FEAT-011 — DDx preserve outcomes from bounded execution attempts (for example failed required executions or ratchet regressions) are not physics-level conflicts. They terminate the current DDx-managed attempt and hand control back to HELIX for escalation, follow-on beads, or user input.\u0026lt;/governing\u0026gt;\u0026#xA;\u0026lt;/context-digest\u0026gt;\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Sparse intake request: \u0026#34;design a CRM\u0026#34;.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Interpretation at autonomy=medium: the user wants HELIX to seed governed planning work for a new CRM product design effort.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Conflict detected during artifact traversal: this repository\u0026#39;s higher-authority frame artifacts define HELIX itself as the product (`docs/helix/01-frame/prd.md`, `workflows/README.md`). Creating CRM vision/PRD/design artifacts directly in this repo would therefore contradict the current product scope unless the request is intended as one of the following:\u0026#xA;- a separate CRM project/repository that should use HELIX\u0026#xA;- a HELIX example/demo artifact pack about CRM design\u0026#xA;- a reinterpretation into HELIX product work rather than a CRM product\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Deterministic next step: obtain the target-project decision before creating downstream CRM frame or design beads.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. The user explicitly chooses whether the CRM work should live in a separate project/repository, in HELIX as an example/demo artifact set, or be reinterpreted as HELIX product work.\u0026#xA;2. The chosen target identifies where governing frame artifacts should live.\u0026#xA;3. Follow-on planning beads can then be created without contradicting `docs/helix/01-frame/prd.md` or `workflows/README.md`.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003cnotes\u003e\nConflict evidence: `docs/helix/01-frame/prd.md` states HELIX is a development control system for AI-assisted software delivery, and `workflows/README.md` defines this repository as the HELIX workflow contract. CRM product artifacts would need a user-confirmed target before downstream frame/design work can be created non-conflictingly at medium autonomy.\n    \u003c/notes\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ehelix, phase:frame, kind:planning, scope:crm, area:docs, area:planning, area:workflow, ac-quality:needs-refinement\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"helix-db7d13a9\" spec-id=\"FEAT-011\" base-rev=\"ef6a52984a173637369899be84627fcde333640a\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260515T004120-a98eb7dd\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"FEAT-011\" path=\"docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-011-slider-autonomy.md\"\u003eFEAT-011: Slider Autonomy Control\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260515T004120-a98eb7dd","base_rev":"ef6a52984a173637369899be84627fcde333640a","bead_id":"helix-dfddd64b","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260515T004120-a98eb7dd","correlation_id":"helix-dfddd64b:20260515T004120-a98eb7dd","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260515T004120-a98eb7dd/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"5b4d23607fbece37b6c520adfcda3d1d8aabfad0e8dbc1b67b087874bdf4c97a","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-07b8b5ab","worker_id":""}}}
